§L The ground of nullity in this and the following section is the impossibility of periorming the act which is the object of the obligation. An act or forbearance either may be impossible ab initio, i. e. at the time at which the contract was made; or it may become impossible subse- quently andex post facto. Original impossibility again may be either ab· solute, as where no one can perform the act (e. g. this section), or relative, as where, though the particular promisor cannot perform it, another can.
